Re: Running on a port other than 8333

Bitcointalk

2010-09-12 17:40:20 UTC - [11]Original Post

   [12]Quote from: lachesis on August 10, 2010, 03:24:55 PM
   [DEL: Also, does Bitcoin open the BerkeleyDB as exclusive, precluding
   the need for a file lock? :DEL] It does not -- did my own tests.
   Is there a way to open BerkeleyDB exclusive?
   DB_PRIVATE is the worst of both worlds.  DB_PRIVATE is not exclusive,
   but it does make it get screwed up if another process tries to access
   it at the same time.
   Iʼve dropped the DB_PRIVATE flag in rev 153.
